node.text:
"Because of climate change we are seeing even more intense storms, rising sea levels and many deaths. But we don’t have to accept this – we can act - and we must act as a matter of justice."

Environmentalist Sunita Narain explains why it's important that all of us #ActNow to achieve the goals of the #ParisAgreement. 

"Every country, rich or poor, is exposed to extreme weather. We need to build better and more resilient infrastructure – from electricity grids to roads, bridges and buildings. All these approaches are set out in the Paris Climate Agreement – adopted by nearly 200 countries. We can do it – we must do it – and we must act quickly."

From recycling to using less energy and water to opting for public transport, each and every one of us can take little steps in our everyday lives that can have a big impact. Tell us in the comments what you are doing to protect our planet.

#ClimateAction #GlobalGoals

"We don’t have to choose between using energy and protecting the planet."

@unep Young Champion of the Earth Nzambi Matee explains the role sustainable energy plays in building a better future for all. 
 
"Imagine a world where every job is based on clean, renewable energy – and where wind and solar are even more abundant. And where energy is affordable and reliable – and available to everyone. This might sound like a fantasy – but it’s achievable and we know how to get there."

The #ParisAgreement on the climate emergency is our roadmap for moving to a low-carbon economy and achieving a sustainable future. Since this international #ClimateAction treaty opened for signature 5 years ago, almost 200 countries have signed on to tackle the climate crisis together to limit global warming to protect people and planet.

 #GlobalGoals #ActNow

"My warmest wishes to everyone celebrating #EidAlFitr," #UnitedNations Secretary-General @antonioguterres said on Wednesday.

"I was delighted to mark the end of Ramadan with Asia El-Sayeed Ali, a Yemeni health worker helping malnourished children and mothers in a @worldfoodprogramme-supported nutrition clinic.

Asia personifies core values of Ramadan: compassion and empathy. Her resilience in the face of the devastating conflict in Yemen, as well as her life-saving work in support of people in desperate need have moved me greatly.

As #Ramadan comes to an end, let us continue drawing inspiration from its many lessons of solidarity that are celebrated during this Holy Month."

Regram: @antonioguterres

Regram: @antonioguterres

Young people are the most affected by the climate decisions taken today. Their ideas, voices and actions are crucial to deliver meaningful and ambitious #ClimateAction for all.

@pcopaloma and @mahery_loha are two inspiring climate activists who exemplify the leadership and commitment of young people worldwide to address the most challenging problems we face today.

I'm grateful for our discussion and their insights on how to achieve the meaningful participation of youth, women and indigenous peoples as we tackle the climate crisis.

#ActNow #GlobalGoals

@unep Goodwill Ambassador @aidanrgallagher describes how the #ParisAgreement can help us create a world free from the threats of the climate crisis. 

"This is personal for me," he explains. "I don’t want to choke on the air I breathe, or see wildfires burning out of control. So let’s keep working together. And you too can protect what is left and repair what has been damaged."

On Thursday's #EarthDay, @antonioguterres will be joining the U.S. Leaders’ Summit on Climate to reiterate his call for urgent #ClimateAction. 

"The Paris Agreement is our pact with our children, grandchildren & the whole human family," said the Secretary-General. 

"The climate crisis is the race of our lifetimes. We must go much further, and much faster."

#GenerationRestoration #ForNature

All children have the right to a happy and healthy childhood, free from discrimination and full of love and acceptance. And acceptance begins at home. Every child should grow up in safe, loving and nurturing environment.

No child should suffer because of who they are. All children deserve protection and equal rights. Let's see kids the way they see themselves.

On Wednesday's International Transgender Day of Visibility, join @unaidsglobal in calling for the rights of transgender children to be protected.

node.text:
A group of girls eagerly raise their hands as they participate in class in #Nigeria.

More than a half a million children are still out of school in the northeast of the country due to ongoing conflict and violence. For internally displaced children, education can ensure their safety and a better future. Yet for many, attending school remains an aspiration out of reach.

@unicef and other humanitarian partners are working to deliver assistance to conflict-affected children, including access to shelter, healthcare, education and more. This year, additional funding will be needed to continue the emergency response and address increasing needs.

Regram: @un_ocha I 📷: UNOCHA/Damilola Onafuwa

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United Nations on August 02, 2021. May be a closeup of 1 person and child.

node.text:
Six-month-old baby Wegahta from #Ethiopia looks at the camera while chewing on her fingers. 

The little one was only six days old when her family fled their home to escape violence in the country’s Tigray region. She is among the 100,000 children facing life-threatening malnutrition due to food shortages and other disruptions caused by ongoing conflict and #COVID19. 

@unicef is working to reach families like Wegahta's with humanitarian assistance including by providing access to lifesaving health care and nutrition supplies.

Regram: @unicef I © UNICEF/UN0494131/Nesbitt

#ForEveryChild #GlobalGoals

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United Nations on August 02, 2021. May be a closeup of nature.

node.text:
Most flowering plant species and many food crops depend on pollinators like this vibrant butterfly. Yet, these guardians of biodiversity are under threat from human activities. 

Our very existence depends on pollinators. They increase food production, give us nutritious food, and are key for achieving the #GlobalGoals. Forest management and other sustainable practices can ensure diverse natural habitats for pollinators and increase agricultural resilience. 

The #UnitedNations Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) is working to safeguard all pollinators and the earth's biodiversity by promoting agricultural activities that are less dependent on toxic chemicals. 

Regram: @fao I 📷: FAO/Nature Kenya/Dino Martins

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United Nations on August 01, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and child.

node.text:
14-year-old Rakia (left) from #Niger was still a very young student when her uncle wanted to marry her. But her grandmother refused. Since then, she has been supported by the #UnitedNations Populations Fund (UNFPA) through mentoring services.

Globally, 1 in every 5 girls gets married before reaching the age of 18. Child marriage exposes girls to violence, including rape, and often forces them to drop out of school and take on the challenges of early motherhood. Girls involved in these marriages are extremely vulnerable and are often unable to advocate for their needs and rights. 

UNFPA is working to #EndChildMarriage and to protect girls like Rakia against lasting trauma including by providing adequate information, skills, and support services. 

Regram: @unfpa I 📸: UNFPA Niger / Ollivier Girard

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United Nations on August 01, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'GROW FOOD AT HOME! #PeterRabbitFoodHero 0066 Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations ACTN'.

node.text:
Peter Rabbit is helping the #UnitedNations build a more sustainable world. He's doing his part to protect our only planet and is asking YOU to become a food hero like him.

From growing your own fruits and vegetables at home to cooking sustainable recipes, composting and wasting less food, all of us can take #ClimateAction in our everyday lives.

Tell us in the comments below what you are doing to protect our planet and our future!

#PeterRabbitFoodHero #ActNow #GlobalGoals

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United Nations on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, child, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
7-year-old Ahmed from #Yemen poses for a photo in Azzhurah, a site for internally displaced people where he and his family now live after having fled their home due to ongoing conflict.

"I want to be a pilot to fly away with my friends," the little boy explains. 

The weather in the area is very hot and displaced families don't have electricity for fans. Most people eat only one or two meals a day, mainly bread and tea.

The #UnitedNations refugee agency (UNHCR) is working to support people in need in Yemen, including with cash assistance programmes, which help put food on the table for many struggling families.

Regram: @refugees I 📸: UNHCR / Shadi Abusneida

https://www.instagram.com/p/CR6LDJmrDT1/

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United Nations on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 9 people, child and outdoors.

node.text:
An elderly woman washes her hands at a newly built water supply and handwashing facility in #Ghana.

Amid the pandemic, her community in the north of the country received two handwashing stations and water tanks, thanks to an initiative led by the #UnitedNations. Access to water is especially beneficial for women in the community, many of whom previously had to travel long distances in search of the commodity.

With #COVID19 posing a threat to people everywhere, access to clean water is vital for hygiene and safety. UN-Habitat is working to improve water service delivery and provide access to water and sanitation to those most in need.

Regram: @unhabitat  I 📸: UN-Habitat/Julius Mwelu

#GlobalGoals

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by United Nations on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and child.

node.text:
School meals and take-home rations serve as an incentive for parents to send their children to school and encourage enrollment. They can transform communities and serve as platforms for improving education and food systems globally. 

The absence of school means put children at risk of: 

🔹 Increased poverty
🔹 Destabilization and migration
🔹 Child marriages 
🔹 Recruitment to extremist groups

Amid the #COVID19 pandemic, the World Food Programme (WFP) has continued to support sustainable national school meals programmes, helping millions of children to stay healthy through nutritious meals and focused on their education. 

Scroll through to see more images of children in #Cambodia enjoying meals at their schools.

Regram: @worldfoodprogramme I 📸: WFP/Nick Sells

#ZeroHunger #GlobalGoals

A woman holding up a photo of relatives who, having left Somaliland with traffickers several years ago, have not been heard from since.

Friday is World Day against Trafficking in Persons.

Human trafficking happens around us, every day. As criminals use increasingly sophisticated methods, including social media, to contact and lure victims, survivors play a key role in the fight and prevention of this terrible crime. We must learn from their experience and listen to their advice.

You can help end human trafficking by highlighting the work of survivors in your country or community and showing your support to #EndHumanTrafficking.

A displaced boy shows his prosthetic leg in #Yemen, having stepped on a landmine near his home.

Last year, children made up a quarter of the civilian casualties from landmines, explosive weapons, and explosive remnants of war. Child survivors experience life-long impairments including amputation, paralysis, and loss of vision and hearing. 

Civilians caught up in conflict are killed and injured in greater numbers than members of fighting forces. In 2020, the #UnitedNations recorded 11,892 civilian casualties in #Afghanistan, #Syria, and Yemen.

The United Nations Mine Action Service (@un_mineaction) is working to reduce danger and protect people from the physical and psychological harm caused by explosive hazards -- and to achieve a world free from the threat of landmines. 

The United Nations office for humanitarian affairs (OCHA) is also working to coordinate assistance for survivors and all families in need.

Three curious tiger cubs are ready to explore their world in Mysore, #India.⠀

Thursday is #TigerDay!

Over the last century the world's tiger population has declined by 95% due to habitat loss and wildlife trafficking. Today, there are more tigers in captivity than in the wild.⠀

Here are some actions you can take to help protect tigers:⠀

- Get informed about the status of wildlife and wildlife products.⠀
- Support companies that demonstrate sustainable supply chains and environmentally responsible policies.⠀
- Don't buy products from wildlife protected by law.⠀
- Spread the word and encourage others to get informed as well.
